data.text:
Prince Alexander of Italy (born Prince Alexander of Yugoslavia on 15 January 1982) is a member of the Italian Royal Family as the husband of Victoria, Princess Piedmont. He is also a member of the Yugoslavian Royal Family as the third and youngest son of Alexander II, King of Yugoslavia and Princess Maria da Gloria of Orleans-Braganza. He is the twin brother of Prince Philip of Yugoslavia.
